Defendant Adam Michael Clark in court with Attorney Bridget Joy Krause.  Defendant Adam Michael Clark in custody.  Irene Elizabeth Parthum appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for a Plea/Sentencing Hearing.  As to Plea:  AS TO COUNT #1:  Defendant advised of constitutional rights and of maximum penalties, waived all rights and plead NO CONTEST.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights received and filed.  Stipulation by state and defense to complaint as factual basis to sustain plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Court found the State has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the state, defense and defendant.  AS TO COUNT #1:  Court sentenced defendant to serve NINE (9) months straight time in the House of Correction with credit for NINETY-THREE (93) days;  The Court STAYS sentence and orders PROBATION for ONE (1) year. 

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. 
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  

Court advised defendant if he is not a citizen of the United States of America, that upon a plea of guilty or no contest for this offense, he could be deported, excluded from admission to his country, or denied naturalization under federal law.  
Court advised that the defendant will have to provide a DNA sample, to the Wisconsin State Crime Laboratory for DNA testing and pay a DNA surcharge.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Random urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - No driving of any vehicle without a valid license;
 - Pay Restitution in the amount of $379.59 to Gary D.  Restitution is to be paid BEFORE surcharges, costs and disbursements; 
 - Defendant also has to pay $928.00 to the Milwaukee County DA's Office for extradiction costs.  This is also to be paid BEFORE surcharges, costs and disbursements.
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements by the end of probationary period. Failure to pay amounts in full will result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Filed,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
